Here are 5 “puzzle pieces” (big historical attempts to unify how complex systems work) and the invariants that survive across all of them. I’ll keep it crisp and “load-bearing.”

The 5 puzzle pieces
	1.	Cybernetics (Wiener/Maxwell lineage)
Core move: control via feedback + communication (steering).  ￼
	2.	General System Theory (Bertalanffy)
Core move: open systems, interaction, equifinality (many paths → same end state).  ￼
	3.	Information Theory (Shannon)
Core move: uncertainty quantified; limits of compression and reliable transmission under noise.  ￼
	4.	Complex Adaptive Systems (SFI / Holland tradition)
Core move: agents adapt in perpetually novel environments; macro order emerges from micro rules.  ￼
	5.	Evolutionary / Game Dynamics + Networks (replicators + structure)
Core move: selection changes population distributions; network topology shapes spread and robustness (hubs, preferential attachment).  ￼

